      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are the quantities of interest. NIH is the standard regulatory metric for blood pump hemolysis assessment per ISO 10993-4. RH < 1 directly encodes the predicate device comparison required by the COU. QoI relevance is high; achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
